1
00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

3
00:00:07,774 --> 00:00:10,077
The second single
will be released soon.

4
00:00:10,244 --> 00:00:13,113
This time,
you must crush that annoying traitor

5
00:00:13,180 --> 00:00:14,481
and get first place!

6
00:00:14,548 --> 00:00:15,749
Stop shouting. Calm down.

7
00:00:15,816 --> 00:00:16,884
How can I be calm?

8
00:00:17,084 --> 00:00:18,919
It'll be your fault if we lose again.

9
00:00:19,653 --> 00:00:21,188
You got deceived by that scammer

10
00:00:21,255 --> 00:00:23,690
just because she's a bit pretty.
How gross!

11
00:00:23,757 --> 00:00:24,958
She did no real harm.

12
00:00:25,025 --> 00:00:26,894
She caused real harm everywhere!

13
00:00:26,960 --> 00:00:29,162
She stole our members'
personal information

14
00:00:29,229 --> 00:00:30,764
and now she even knows
our current situation!

15
00:00:30,831 --> 00:00:32,533
She knew we were poor to begin with.

16
00:00:32,599 --> 00:00:35,602
Shut up! Why did you treat
that jerk to hot pot?

17
00:00:35,669 --> 00:00:38,939
That's our money. It's frustrating!

18
00:00:39,006 --> 00:00:40,173
Stingy.

19
00:00:41,942 --> 00:00:43,277
Don't call me stingy!

20
00:00:43,343 --> 00:00:45,946
Okay! I give up... Gosh!

21
00:00:46,780 --> 00:00:48,382
If we lose to TORINNER

22
00:00:48,448 --> 00:00:50,751
and that detestable Park Ji-soo
next time

23
00:00:51,752 --> 00:00:53,987
I won't be able to pay off
the 500 million debt.

24
00:00:54,488 --> 00:00:58,125
Then, the bad guys will capture me,
and I'll become fish food!

25
00:00:58,191 --> 00:00:59,493
My condolences!

26
00:00:59,560 --> 00:01:00,694
Stupid Azuma!

27
00:01:00,761 --> 00:01:03,130
Get first place at all costs! First!

28
00:01:03,196 --> 00:01:05,999
Or MAMA's Best New Artist Award
will be nothing but a pipe dream.

29
00:01:07,935 --> 00:01:09,870
We'll aim for MAMA's
Best New Artist Award.

30
00:01:09,937 --> 00:01:11,405
We can win it!

31
00:01:11,505 --> 00:01:12,506
Yes!

32
00:01:12,573 --> 00:01:14,775
This time, we'll make it to MAMA.

33
00:01:14,841 --> 00:01:17,511
You and SEVEN SEAS failed
to fulfill that dream.

34
00:01:18,512 --> 00:01:21,515
You'll take NAZE to MAMA, right?

35
00:01:22,215 --> 00:01:23,250
Yeah.

36
00:01:24,551 --> 00:01:25,652
This time

37
00:01:26,954 --> 00:01:29,156
I'll take them to that dream stage.

38
00:01:39,199 --> 00:01:40,534
Look at all of those.

39
00:01:45,772 --> 00:01:48,742
This is Mr. Kamiya, the director of

40
00:01:48,809 --> 00:01:49,977
the Japan branch of Bouquet Music.

41
00:01:50,043 --> 00:01:51,511
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

42
00:01:51,578 --> 00:01:52,779
No need for the formalities.

43
00:01:52,846 --> 00:01:54,748
Artists like you two

44
00:01:54,815 --> 00:01:57,951
don't need to be so polite
to an ordinary guy like me.

45
00:01:58,018 --> 00:01:59,019
Have a seat.

46
00:02:03,523 --> 00:02:06,259
I apologize for making you come
all the way here.

47
00:02:06,593 --> 00:02:09,863
Today, I'd like to talk to you
about TORINNER

48
00:02:09,930 --> 00:02:14,334
as well as the roadmap
we've planned for the group.

49
00:02:16,169 --> 00:02:19,973
Our CEO, Mr. Choi Ki-young,
has high expectations for TORINNER.

50
00:02:20,574 --> 00:02:23,176
He's considering
a huge global development

51
00:02:23,243 --> 00:02:25,679
that's beyond
the other agencies' imagination.

52
00:02:25,746 --> 00:02:27,514
After the release
of their second single

53
00:02:27,581 --> 00:02:29,216
they will release a full album
in July

54
00:02:29,282 --> 00:02:32,152
and they will be holding a world tour
including US stops.

55
00:02:32,219 --> 00:02:33,220
After that...

56
00:02:33,954 --> 00:02:36,289
I can't reveal who it is

57
00:02:36,356 --> 00:02:38,358
but they will be
having a collaboration

58
00:02:38,425 --> 00:02:39,793
with a world-famous artist.

59
00:02:40,494 --> 00:02:41,628
Wow!

60
00:02:41,695 --> 00:02:45,365
In November, they'll receive
MAMA's Best New Artist Award.

61
00:02:45,432 --> 00:02:48,535
I can safely say
everything will go as planned.

62
00:02:48,602 --> 00:02:50,937
MAMA? You mean that MAMA?

63
00:02:51,004 --> 00:02:52,005
That's right!

64
00:02:52,939 --> 00:02:54,741
The MAMA Awards.

65
00:02:54,808 --> 00:02:58,545
It is the biggest K-pop award
ceremony known worldwide.

66
00:02:58,612 --> 00:03:03,083
All K-pop artists long
to stand on the stage there.

67
00:03:03,150 --> 00:03:04,251
Am I right, Kun?

68
00:03:04,584 --> 00:03:06,853
TORINNER will stand
on the MAMA's stage...

69
00:03:06,920 --> 00:03:08,755
- It's not decided--
- That's right!

70
00:03:08,989 --> 00:03:10,957
After all, we...

71
00:03:11,024 --> 00:03:14,928
Bouquet Music, are going all out
to support TORINNER.

72
00:03:15,762 --> 00:03:19,700
Our company's principle is
to give artists

73
00:03:19,766 --> 00:03:21,902
the greatest respect and love.

74
00:03:21,968 --> 00:03:25,839
That's especially true for extremely
talented people such as you two.

75
00:03:27,140 --> 00:03:29,309
What do you say?

76
00:03:30,210 --> 00:03:33,246
Have you decided to join TORINNER?

77
00:03:45,659 --> 00:03:46,660
No.

78
00:03:47,794 --> 00:03:50,897
We came here today to turn you down.

79
00:03:51,898 --> 00:03:54,868
Is that so? Why is that?

80
00:03:55,469 --> 00:03:58,739
The reason we've made it
this far is that

81
00:03:58,805 --> 00:04:01,141
we've learned many things
from Mr. Azuma.

82
00:04:03,110 --> 00:04:06,880
We trust Mr. Azuma very much, so...

83
00:04:09,850 --> 00:04:11,184
I see.

84
00:04:12,319 --> 00:04:15,589
You two are very honest.

85
00:04:17,691 --> 00:04:18,825
But...

86
00:04:21,027 --> 00:04:24,564
If you continue to trust Mr. Azuma

87
00:04:25,098 --> 00:04:26,433
you'll regret it.

88
00:04:28,969 --> 00:04:32,072
This is an article in a tabloid
five years ago.

89
00:04:34,574 --> 00:04:38,044
Azuma abused the group
he was training back then

90
00:04:38,111 --> 00:04:40,313
so he was banned from the industry.

91
00:04:41,982 --> 00:04:45,585
There was no uproar
since his agency pulled some strings

92
00:04:46,686 --> 00:04:51,057
but lately, people get bashed
horribly for past incidents.

93
00:04:51,124 --> 00:04:54,528
What will happen if a similar article
sees the light of the day again?

94
00:04:55,128 --> 00:04:59,900
Don't forget that NAZE is currently
on the rise.

95
00:04:59,966 --> 00:05:01,868
What about your mother's
medical expenses

96
00:05:01,935 --> 00:05:04,471
and your little brother's
living expenses?

97
00:05:05,138 --> 00:05:10,277
Humans need money to survive.

98
00:05:20,120 --> 00:05:22,656
Is this article true?

99
00:05:24,891 --> 00:05:27,694
Those kids aren't interested at all!

100
00:05:27,761 --> 00:05:31,031
All this dawdling is
the reason you were fired!

101
00:05:32,732 --> 00:05:36,369
As instructed, I infiltrated NAZE
to create chaos

102
00:05:36,436 --> 00:05:39,039
and asked Turn and Kimkun
to join TORINNER.

103
00:05:39,105 --> 00:05:40,273
Good work.

104
00:05:41,274 --> 00:05:43,877
As it happens, we also have
two rotten apples in TORINNER.

105
00:05:45,378 --> 00:05:46,646
We'll swap them.

106
00:05:50,450 --> 00:05:51,451
No.

107
00:05:52,786 --> 00:05:56,823
I don't think they'll agree
to join TORINNER.

108
00:05:57,457 --> 00:05:59,392
Hey, what are you talking about?

109
00:06:02,863 --> 00:06:05,398
You call them losers and leftovers

110
00:06:05,465 --> 00:06:07,334
but they've united
under Producer Azuma

111
00:06:07,400 --> 00:06:09,002
and formed a family-like bond.

112
00:06:09,603 --> 00:06:13,106
If you make two TORINNER members quit
and add the two NAZE members

113
00:06:13,173 --> 00:06:15,375
it'll upset them
and have the opposite effect.

114
00:06:16,376 --> 00:06:19,646
It would be smarter not
to steal the NAZE members.

115
00:06:19,713 --> 00:06:21,982
You're just a mere producer.
How dare you talk like that?

116
00:06:22,048 --> 00:06:28,488
Ms. Park, are you saying
you oppose my plan?

117
00:06:28,555 --> 00:06:33,126
No, this is just a realistic analysis
of the situation.

118
00:06:40,700 --> 00:06:42,002
Thanks.

119
00:06:43,103 --> 00:06:46,206
Not many people will
voice their opinions to me now.

120
00:06:49,776 --> 00:06:52,379
We need to cherish talents
like her...

121
00:06:52,979 --> 00:06:54,247
Mr. Kamiya.

122
00:06:54,748 --> 00:06:56,716
You're right, Mr. Choi.

123
00:06:57,350 --> 00:06:58,485
Well, then.

124
00:06:59,619 --> 00:07:01,655
From now on,
TORINNER's chief producer...

125
00:07:03,690 --> 00:07:05,292
will be Mr. Kamiya.

126
00:07:06,693 --> 00:07:07,694
What?

127
00:07:08,128 --> 00:07:11,398
Ms. Park, you'll assist him

128
00:07:12,032 --> 00:07:14,701
and continue to train the group.

129
00:07:16,102 --> 00:07:18,405
I'm in all this trouble
thanks to you.

130
00:07:18,471 --> 00:07:20,507
I'm a businessman

131
00:07:20,573 --> 00:07:23,376
and I don't want to do creative work.

132
00:07:24,144 --> 00:07:25,312
Still...

133
00:07:27,147 --> 00:07:28,949
Since I'm in charge now

134
00:07:29,015 --> 00:07:33,453
I need to train them again
from scratch into cash cows.

135
00:07:35,488 --> 00:07:36,523
Here he is.

136
00:07:36,756 --> 00:07:37,757
Come in.

137
00:07:40,527 --> 00:07:42,062
Pleased to meet you, Mr. Kamiya.

138
00:07:42,529 --> 00:07:44,631
I'm Seso Weekly's Kazamatsuri.

139
00:07:44,798 --> 00:07:46,232
Please have a seat.

140
00:07:47,133 --> 00:07:49,836
I'm asking you...

141
00:07:49,903 --> 00:07:53,073
Why did I have to treat
that liar to hot pot?

142
00:07:53,139 --> 00:07:55,709
What are you here for?
You're blathering on and on.

143
00:07:55,775 --> 00:07:58,411
What's wrong with coming
to have dinner?

144
00:07:58,478 --> 00:07:59,879
Why do I need your permission?

145
00:07:59,946 --> 00:08:00,947
This is my home.

146
00:08:01,014 --> 00:08:03,049
Besides, you're one to talk!

147
00:08:03,116 --> 00:08:06,252
You got totally deceived
by that scammer. How gross!

148
00:08:06,319 --> 00:08:08,488
What do you like
about that ugly woman? How gross!

149
00:08:08,555 --> 00:08:12,058
The song Ms. Park bought
is awesome, isn't it?

150
00:08:12,125 --> 00:08:14,127
I wouldn't have been able to get it.

151
00:08:14,194 --> 00:08:16,029
Besides, I like her. She's pretty.

152
00:08:16,096 --> 00:08:18,531
Like her? Pretty?

153
00:08:18,598 --> 00:08:21,267
Anyway, you're too careless!

154
00:08:21,334 --> 00:08:22,936
Nowadays, information is everything!

155
00:08:23,003 --> 00:08:24,838
She now knows
our members' special talents

156
00:08:24,904 --> 00:08:25,905
and what they can't do.

157
00:08:25,972 --> 00:08:27,674
- She won't resort to cheap tricks.
- You're too naive!

158
00:08:27,741 --> 00:08:30,543
That's why we're losing to TORINNER,
you third-rate producer!

159
00:08:30,610 --> 00:08:32,979
Come again, you third-rate CEO?

160
00:08:33,046 --> 00:08:35,081
You're the only one
who would be so rude to me!

161
00:08:35,148 --> 00:08:36,483
You're the only one!

162
00:08:37,617 --> 00:08:40,086
Third-rate CEO?

163
00:08:40,153 --> 00:08:42,489
- What... Hey...
- You little...

164
00:08:42,555 --> 00:08:44,024
Wait...

165
00:08:44,090 --> 00:08:46,593
- Wait! Come on...
- Unforgivable!

166
00:08:46,659 --> 00:08:48,695
Can an adult intervene?

167
00:08:50,230 --> 00:08:51,331
I can't ask them...

168
00:08:59,205 --> 00:09:00,206
Excuse me, Ms. Nam.

169
00:09:00,273 --> 00:09:04,711
How long have you and Mr. Azuma
been in a relationship?

170
00:09:04,778 --> 00:09:06,212
Wait, why are you asking that
out of nowhere?

171
00:09:06,279 --> 00:09:09,516
Nothing! There is no specific reason.

172
00:09:13,820 --> 00:09:16,022
Let me think. About 10 years.

173
00:09:16,089 --> 00:09:17,323
Ten years?

174
00:09:17,557 --> 00:09:19,626
I mean our relationship
as colleagues.

175
00:09:20,260 --> 00:09:22,629
No, that's not what I mean.

176
00:09:23,763 --> 00:09:24,898
I mean your romantic relationship.

177
00:09:24,964 --> 00:09:27,100
Let's see...

178
00:09:27,767 --> 00:09:29,769
- About 15 years?
- 15 years!

179
00:09:30,303 --> 00:09:32,472
Why is it even longer?

180
00:09:32,539 --> 00:09:34,874
I mean, I think of him as my lover
only in my mind.

181
00:09:34,941 --> 00:09:36,910
I've been in love with him
since university.

182
00:09:36,976 --> 00:09:38,311
That's not what I'm asking.

183
00:09:39,212 --> 00:09:40,213
Did you two actually date?

184
00:09:40,280 --> 00:09:43,149
What? Minase,
are you in love with Azuma?

185
00:09:43,983 --> 00:09:44,984
Yes...

186
00:09:46,686 --> 00:09:49,289
What? No, I'm not.

187
00:09:49,355 --> 00:09:52,158
You're better off
not dating that guy.

188
00:09:52,225 --> 00:09:55,462
He can't take care of himself,
and nobody knows what he's thinking.

189
00:09:55,528 --> 00:09:57,397
Wait. I mean, it isn't like that.

190
00:09:57,464 --> 00:10:02,702
I respect Mr. Azuma as a producer.

191
00:10:02,769 --> 00:10:04,671
Is that so? But...

192
00:10:05,939 --> 00:10:08,274
He can be quite romantic, you know?

193
00:10:09,209 --> 00:10:11,978
I wonder if he still has it.

194
00:10:12,145 --> 00:10:15,949
That one thing
filled with our fond memories.

195
00:10:16,015 --> 00:10:17,016
"That one thing"?

196
00:10:18,051 --> 00:10:19,419
What is that?

197
00:10:22,155 --> 00:10:24,791
If Azuma still has that

198
00:10:24,858 --> 00:10:28,661
then maybe he still
has feelings for me.

199
00:10:30,196 --> 00:10:31,364
What are you talking about?

200
00:10:31,431 --> 00:10:33,066
I can't tell you.

201
00:10:36,870 --> 00:10:37,971
What was she talking about?

202
00:10:39,038 --> 00:10:40,473
Wait, what is it?

203
00:10:41,774 --> 00:10:46,546
One, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight.

204
00:10:48,481 --> 00:10:50,150
Your moves are not sharp at all!

205
00:10:50,216 --> 00:10:52,152
I told you to always pay attention
to the fans.

206
00:10:52,218 --> 00:10:54,954
Can you beat TORINNER like that?
Do it once more!

207
00:10:55,021 --> 00:10:56,156
- Yes, sir!
- Yes, sir!

208
00:10:56,856 --> 00:10:58,925
It feels like Mr. Azuma is
taking charge

209
00:10:58,992 --> 00:11:00,460
for the first time in a while.

210
00:11:00,527 --> 00:11:01,861
Yeah, he's taking this seriously.

211
00:11:01,928 --> 00:11:03,897
This suits Mr. Azuma more.

212
00:11:03,963 --> 00:11:06,499
- Younki, Kaisei, drink your water!
- Yes, sir!

213
00:11:06,566 --> 00:11:07,567
Yes, sir!

214
00:11:07,901 --> 00:11:10,136
- Run faster!
- Yes, sir!

215
00:11:10,203 --> 00:11:12,705
About 30 seconds left.
Let's keep this up!

216
00:11:12,772 --> 00:11:15,775
- Okay!
- Mr. Azuma!

217
00:11:16,509 --> 00:11:19,412
Park Ji-soo:
Let's talk about the contract.

218
00:11:25,952 --> 00:11:27,353
Excuse me, Mr. Azuma.

219
00:11:27,787 --> 00:11:32,625
Are you perhaps keeping something
important somewhere in this house?

220
00:11:33,459 --> 00:11:36,963
What? Why do you ask?
I have nothing valuable.

221
00:11:39,532 --> 00:11:40,733
I thought so.

222
00:11:40,800 --> 00:11:42,802
You got banned from the industry,
and you're in debt.

223
00:11:42,869 --> 00:11:44,237
Why would you have anything valuable?

224
00:11:44,304 --> 00:11:45,505
That stings.

225
00:11:46,539 --> 00:11:49,642
Still, there are things that aren't
valuable but important to me.

226
00:11:51,077 --> 00:11:52,645
What do you mean?

227
00:11:52,712 --> 00:11:55,215
Well, things that contain memories
with the people I cherish.

228
00:11:55,281 --> 00:11:56,449
Like Kun's.

229
00:11:56,516 --> 00:11:57,884
What? Oh, right.

230
00:11:58,551 --> 00:12:01,287
My mom made me this.

231
00:12:01,354 --> 00:12:02,855
We all get stuff like that.

232
00:12:02,922 --> 00:12:05,792
For me, it's the love letters
I received in the past.

233
00:12:05,892 --> 00:12:06,893
- What?
- What?

234
00:12:06,960 --> 00:12:09,596
Or stickers I got
from the girl I liked.

235
00:12:09,662 --> 00:12:14,100
So boys do tend to cherish
fond memories they share with girls.

236
00:12:14,434 --> 00:12:15,435
I need to check.

237
00:12:15,501 --> 00:12:19,272
Right, I also keep things to
remind myself of the mistakes I made.

238
00:12:19,339 --> 00:12:20,673
Like exam papers with bad scores!

239
00:12:20,740 --> 00:12:23,843
That's just hiding it. You were
going to destroy the evidence.

240
00:12:23,910 --> 00:12:25,378
Where did you learn that?

241
00:12:25,445 --> 00:12:27,981
In Japan, we stuff those
in snack cans.

242
00:12:28,047 --> 00:12:29,249
Yeah, you're right!

243
00:12:29,315 --> 00:12:31,184
I used to hide important stuff
in snack cans.

244
00:12:31,251 --> 00:12:35,755
I see! They hide important things
in snack cans.

245
00:12:35,822 --> 00:12:37,290
We do that in Korea too!

246
00:12:37,457 --> 00:12:41,027
We hide it under the bed,
but our mothers end up finding it!

247
00:12:41,094 --> 00:12:43,830
But there aren't any beds
in this house.

248
00:12:43,963 --> 00:12:44,964
What about Thai people?

249
00:12:45,031 --> 00:12:46,966
We hide it above Buddhist altars.

250
00:12:47,800 --> 00:12:50,003
In Japan, people commonly hide
stuff under the floor

251
00:12:50,069 --> 00:12:52,538
under the roof,
and in the toilet's water tank.

252
00:12:53,139 --> 00:12:56,476
Under the floor, under the roof,
and in the toilet's water tank.

253
00:12:57,176 --> 00:12:58,578
I'll check those places first.

254
00:12:59,312 --> 00:13:01,814
I keep my fond memories
I've made with NAZE, too.

255
00:13:02,682 --> 00:13:05,818
First, our TGC entry badge.

256
00:13:06,586 --> 00:13:09,088
Next, the bandana I used back then,
which I haven't washed.

257
00:13:09,155 --> 00:13:10,757
And also, the sock at Melody!

258
00:13:10,823 --> 00:13:13,059
- What?
- Wash them!

259
00:13:13,126 --> 00:13:14,661
"Your body is a mirror
of your habits."

260
00:13:14,727 --> 00:13:16,062
What's that? Never heard of it.

261
00:13:16,129 --> 00:13:18,197
It's a popular saying in Nagano.

262
00:13:18,264 --> 00:13:20,600
That's too obscure!

263
00:13:20,667 --> 00:13:22,502
- What are you doing?
- Put them back!

264
00:13:22,568 --> 00:13:23,603
Put them away!

265
00:13:25,371 --> 00:13:28,274
We've become a great team.

266
00:13:28,341 --> 00:13:32,478
Right. I was so worried
when I first arrived at this house.

267
00:13:32,545 --> 00:13:33,613
Right back at you!

268
00:13:33,680 --> 00:13:35,548
It's all thanks
to your help, Mr. Azuma.

269
00:13:35,615 --> 00:13:38,151
That's right. We couldn't have
done this without you, Mr. Azuma.

270
00:13:39,485 --> 00:13:41,487
Say that after you get first place.

271
00:13:42,322 --> 00:13:44,757
- Okay.
- You're right.

272
00:13:44,824 --> 00:13:49,162
Okay! Let's get first place together
with our next song!

273
00:13:49,228 --> 00:13:50,697
- Yes!
- Let's do this!

274
00:13:50,763 --> 00:13:52,131
- Yes!
- Let's do it!

275
00:13:52,198 --> 00:13:53,199
We'll get first place!

276
00:13:53,266 --> 00:13:54,634
- Eat up!
- Okay!

277
00:13:57,103 --> 00:13:58,438
Go ahead.

278
00:14:00,540 --> 00:14:01,607
It's freezing.

279
00:14:01,674 --> 00:14:04,811
- What's the matter?
- Sorry, we'll be a bit late today.

280
00:14:04,944 --> 00:14:07,146
Something happened back home.

281
00:14:08,481 --> 00:14:09,515
Me too.

282
00:14:09,582 --> 00:14:11,017
Let's go, then!

283
00:14:11,084 --> 00:14:12,985
- Okay!
- Let's go!

284
00:14:13,052 --> 00:14:14,387
See you later!

285
00:14:14,454 --> 00:14:16,222
Bye!

286
00:14:32,372 --> 00:14:34,807
Snack cans...

287
00:14:36,576 --> 00:14:37,677
All right...

288
00:14:38,678 --> 00:14:41,681
Snack cans...

289
00:14:42,615 --> 00:14:45,518
Snack... cans!

290
00:14:50,022 --> 00:14:51,724
There we go...

291
00:14:55,762 --> 00:14:57,563
No way!

292
00:15:01,634 --> 00:15:04,804
I don't see snack cans anywhere.

293
00:15:11,811 --> 00:15:14,280
It's... a snack can.

294
00:15:28,294 --> 00:15:30,563
TO MR. AZUMA JUN

295
00:15:35,334 --> 00:15:37,737
We're here. What now?

296
00:15:40,106 --> 00:15:42,442
I want to stay in NAZE.

297
00:15:42,575 --> 00:15:44,243
Me too, but...

298
00:15:46,512 --> 00:15:48,748
If that article
about Mr. Azuma spreads...

299
00:15:49,248 --> 00:15:50,416
We'll have to disband.

300
00:15:59,392 --> 00:16:00,693
We're here.

301
00:16:01,327 --> 00:16:03,229
Wait, aren't they NAZE?

302
00:16:08,134 --> 00:16:10,369
I'm going to the restroom.

303
00:16:10,636 --> 00:16:11,904
Me too.

304
00:16:15,875 --> 00:16:18,611
- Are you okay?
- Hey, are you okay?

305
00:16:18,678 --> 00:16:20,746
- Yeon-woo? Yeon-woo!
- Yeon-woo!

306
00:16:20,813 --> 00:16:23,416
- Are you okay?
- What's wrong? Hey!

307
00:16:24,183 --> 00:16:25,284
Are you okay?

308
00:16:26,285 --> 00:16:27,520
Yeon-woo?

309
00:16:35,328 --> 00:16:37,563
You're late! How dare you slack off?

310
00:16:38,498 --> 00:16:41,834
Come on. Hey, stand up!

311
00:16:41,901 --> 00:16:43,402
You're in the way!

312
00:16:44,504 --> 00:16:45,705
Hey!

313
00:16:46,506 --> 00:16:48,040
That's enough!

314
00:16:49,075 --> 00:16:50,409
This is not practice.

315
00:16:50,676 --> 00:16:51,978
What?

316
00:16:52,144 --> 00:16:54,213
You can quit if you want, you know?

317
00:16:54,280 --> 00:16:57,717
Hey. If you want to put on airs
and act like an artist

318
00:16:57,783 --> 00:17:00,253
do it after you earn some money!

319
00:17:03,523 --> 00:17:06,025
I have an important
business meeting now.

320
00:17:06,359 --> 00:17:08,694
You guys had better
practice properly!

321
00:17:10,730 --> 00:17:11,864
Yeon-woo!

322
00:17:12,231 --> 00:17:13,966
Hey, Ryo. Are you okay?

323
00:17:14,033 --> 00:17:16,469
- Why are you here?
- Ms. Park asked us to come.

324
00:17:16,536 --> 00:17:18,404
Anyway, that old man is so nasty!

325
00:17:19,138 --> 00:17:20,373
Does Ms. Park know?

326
00:17:22,475 --> 00:17:24,644
She's suffering the most right now.

327
00:17:24,810 --> 00:17:25,811
What?

328
00:17:25,878 --> 00:17:29,749
They want to get rid of Nicc and me
and replace us with you two.

329
00:17:29,815 --> 00:17:31,918
And if that doesn't work,
they'll swap us back again.

330
00:17:32,552 --> 00:17:36,022
To them, we're disposables
that can be thrown away after use.

331
00:17:37,590 --> 00:17:41,027
It's not right
to fire TORINNER members

332
00:17:41,093 --> 00:17:42,428
just to take in the NAZE members.

333
00:17:42,495 --> 00:17:44,030
They are not robots.

334
00:17:44,931 --> 00:17:46,966
They have a bond
that they forged together.

335
00:17:47,033 --> 00:17:48,801
That's why they look cohesive.

336
00:17:49,602 --> 00:17:51,837
We should continue
with the same members.

337
00:17:54,807 --> 00:17:55,875
Are you saying this

338
00:17:55,942 --> 00:17:59,912
just because you're a super-famous
producer known worldwide?

339
00:18:02,114 --> 00:18:03,816
Our job is

340
00:18:04,383 --> 00:18:08,821
to properly execute any orders
from Mr. Choi. That's all.

341
00:18:08,888 --> 00:18:10,723
Do your job as instructed.

342
00:18:11,324 --> 00:18:13,826
That's all you're expected to do!

343
00:18:15,227 --> 00:18:20,666
This is the only way
for your beloved TORINNER to survive.

344
00:18:24,437 --> 00:18:27,206
Good, I've been expecting you.

345
00:18:27,273 --> 00:18:29,909
Thank you for coming
all the way here.

346
00:18:30,409 --> 00:18:34,280
Wait, you'll be one of us
starting today, right?

347
00:18:34,347 --> 00:18:35,648
We refuse!

348
00:18:36,582 --> 00:18:40,052
What's the matter?
You must've seen the signing bonus.

349
00:18:40,786 --> 00:18:43,889
Now you don't have
to worry about your family.

350
00:18:43,956 --> 00:18:45,091
Don't be ridiculous!

351
00:18:45,858 --> 00:18:48,260
You were absolutely horrible
to TORINNER!

352
00:18:49,962 --> 00:18:51,497
I see...

353
00:18:51,664 --> 00:18:52,999
Have you met them?

354
00:18:53,065 --> 00:18:54,367
You use the power of money

355
00:18:55,101 --> 00:18:57,970
to trample on
other people's feelings.

356
00:18:59,138 --> 00:19:00,473
We can't work with you.

357
00:19:00,873 --> 00:19:03,442
We'll follow Mr. Azuma.

358
00:19:05,111 --> 00:19:07,613
Are you really sure about this,
you brats?

359
00:19:08,180 --> 00:19:09,682
Don't regret it.

360
00:19:14,787 --> 00:19:16,722
It's over for Azuma.

361
00:19:17,490 --> 00:19:19,091
The same goes for NAZE, too.

362
00:19:26,666 --> 00:19:27,767
Hey, you.

363
00:19:30,136 --> 00:19:32,371
I'm in a very good mood today.

364
00:19:33,706 --> 00:19:34,807
I'll give this to you.

365
00:19:36,542 --> 00:19:37,677
Thank you.

366
00:19:41,447 --> 00:19:42,581
You're funny.

367
00:19:44,583 --> 00:19:45,651
So funny!

368
00:19:57,897 --> 00:19:59,465
TO MR. AZUMA JUN

369
00:20:01,534 --> 00:20:02,635
This should be the place.

370
00:20:10,409 --> 00:20:12,678
Good morning.
Now, for today's morning news.

371
00:20:12,945 --> 00:20:16,182
A music producer who used violence
and abused his power in the past

372
00:20:16,248 --> 00:20:17,783
and caused a controversy

373
00:20:17,850 --> 00:20:19,952
is suspected of doing the same

374
00:20:20,019 --> 00:20:24,724
to the popular boys' group, NAZE,
as reported by multiple magazines.

375
00:20:24,790 --> 00:20:30,029
This producer used
to train SEVEN SEAS

376
00:20:30,096 --> 00:20:32,131
a global boy group that was
active in Japan and Korea

377
00:20:32,198 --> 00:20:34,266
and he used violence and forced them
to attend intense training sessions.

378
00:20:34,333 --> 00:20:36,969
He was speculated to be the reason
behind the group's disbandment.

379
00:20:37,036 --> 00:20:40,940
Now, he is criticized for allegedly
repeating the same coaching style...

380
00:20:42,408 --> 00:20:43,943
It must be Choi Ki-young.

381
00:20:44,643 --> 00:20:46,545
Why is he going this far?

382
00:20:47,279 --> 00:20:48,280
Who knows?

383
00:20:49,281 --> 00:20:51,484
I have no idea how I pissed him off.

384
00:20:54,653 --> 00:20:57,690
It's high time I leave.

385
00:20:58,157 --> 00:21:01,060
Wait! Just tell them it's all false!

386
00:21:01,127 --> 00:21:04,196
We'll be stuck with the mudslinging
for months if I do that!

387
00:21:04,263 --> 00:21:05,931
If that happens,
NAZE won't be able to win.

388
00:21:06,799 --> 00:21:10,035
Choi Ki-young must've been
waiting for the right time.

389
00:21:10,102 --> 00:21:12,505
So that I'd think
leaving is the only way.

390
00:21:13,672 --> 00:21:16,942
If I stay, I'll be in NAZE's way.

391
00:21:17,543 --> 00:21:19,445
This is a crucial time for them.

392
00:21:19,512 --> 00:21:20,546
But...

393
00:21:20,946 --> 00:21:22,948
What am I supposed to tell the boys?

394
00:21:24,617 --> 00:21:26,585
They won't accept it easily.

395
00:21:31,490 --> 00:21:33,793
- This is a lie, right?
- Have you heard anything?

396
00:21:34,193 --> 00:21:35,227
Nothing.

397
00:21:37,730 --> 00:21:41,867
But many people commented they could
tell it was fake right away.

398
00:21:41,934 --> 00:21:45,070
That's right.
I'm sure Mr. Azuma isn't like that.

399
00:21:45,137 --> 00:21:46,906
But at this rate, we...

400
00:21:49,942 --> 00:21:51,410
The most important thing now

401
00:21:51,477 --> 00:21:53,913
is to get first place
with our second single.

402
00:21:54,480 --> 00:21:57,383
Stop overthinking
and get on with our practice.

403
00:21:58,184 --> 00:21:59,218
I agree.

404
00:22:01,887 --> 00:22:05,591
It's over for Azuma.
The same goes for NAZE, too.

405
00:22:20,806 --> 00:22:21,807
Hey.

406
00:22:28,280 --> 00:22:30,049
I am really sorry.

407
00:22:30,115 --> 00:22:32,051
It's not something
you need to apologize for.

408
00:22:32,785 --> 00:22:35,120
I'm the one to blame for it.

409
00:22:40,426 --> 00:22:42,461
It's not my place to say this

410
00:22:43,863 --> 00:22:45,231
but please don't lose.

411
00:22:45,297 --> 00:22:46,699
Of course.

412
00:22:47,633 --> 00:22:48,901
We won't lose.

413
00:22:50,469 --> 00:22:54,206
This moment is crucial to NAZE now.

414
00:22:54,273 --> 00:22:58,344
Choi Ki-young did strike
at the perfect time, though.

415
00:23:07,219 --> 00:23:08,554
I'll disappear.

416
00:23:13,058 --> 00:23:15,394
But that's exactly what Choi wants!

417
00:23:15,461 --> 00:23:18,097
Still, there is no other way
to protect them.

418
00:23:19,031 --> 00:23:20,065
Right?

419
00:23:26,472 --> 00:23:29,141
I enjoyed myself
more than I expected.

420
00:23:32,077 --> 00:23:34,546
At first, I thought they were
completely hopeless.

421
00:23:34,980 --> 00:23:38,584
But now, they've become a team
that's good enough to compete

422
00:23:38,651 --> 00:23:40,119
with elite groups like TORINNER.

423
00:23:40,853 --> 00:23:42,454
They worked hard for it.

424
00:23:44,390 --> 00:23:45,658
Really...

425
00:23:47,893 --> 00:23:49,828
They did a really good job.

426
00:23:50,996 --> 00:23:53,332
I never imagined
they would improve so much.

427
00:23:54,166 --> 00:23:55,968
I abandoned everything

428
00:23:56,035 --> 00:23:59,305
and couldn't find my life's purpose,
so I was wasting away my life.

429
00:23:59,371 --> 00:24:01,974
The seven of them
were the ones who made me

430
00:24:02,708 --> 00:24:03,876
want to live my life to the fullest.

431
00:24:05,644 --> 00:24:06,679
That's why...

432
00:24:08,447 --> 00:24:11,216
I won't do anything
that will waste their efforts.

433
00:24:12,651 --> 00:24:15,054
That's the one thing I must do.

434
00:24:20,059 --> 00:24:24,129
I'm very sorry
that I couldn't stop Choi.

435
00:24:25,497 --> 00:24:28,400
You'll be in serious trouble
if anyone finds out you met with me.

436
00:24:29,535 --> 00:24:30,803
Thanks for coming.

437
00:24:32,905 --> 00:24:36,141
I met you
and came across that great song.

438
00:24:36,842 --> 00:24:39,111
And now, NAZE has grown
even stronger.

439
00:24:39,845 --> 00:24:41,647
NAZE is strong now, you know?

440
00:24:45,684 --> 00:24:47,453
I'll help NAZE climb to the top.

441
00:24:49,822 --> 00:24:51,657
That's my last job.

442
00:24:52,091 --> 00:24:54,426
One, two, three, four

443
00:24:54,493 --> 00:24:56,895
five, six, seven, eight.

444
00:24:56,962 --> 00:25:00,165
One, two, three, four, five, six...

445
00:25:00,232 --> 00:25:02,634
We weren't in sync just now.
Concentrate!

446
00:25:02,701 --> 00:25:03,802
- Okay!
- Yes.

447
00:25:03,869 --> 00:25:06,372
Five, six, seven, eight.

448
00:25:06,438 --> 00:25:08,741
One, two, three, four...

449
00:25:17,383 --> 00:25:18,717
There's no need to hesitate.

450
00:25:19,818 --> 00:25:21,220
That's right.

451
00:25:22,254 --> 00:25:23,555
Crush them.

452
00:25:31,430 --> 00:25:32,564
Minase!

453
00:25:36,168 --> 00:25:37,536
What happened?

454
00:25:43,175 --> 00:25:45,944
Hey, what's wrong, Minase?

455
00:26:16,942 --> 00:26:18,043
What's this?

456
00:26:20,579 --> 00:26:21,580
RIKU, LEADER OF SS, DIES BY SUICIDE

457
00:26:21,880 --> 00:26:23,115
Suicide?

458
00:26:25,617 --> 00:26:28,921
"It has been discovered that Riku,
leader of the popular idol group SS

459
00:26:28,987 --> 00:26:31,323
passed away four years ago.

460
00:26:32,224 --> 00:26:36,095
His family says he committed
suicide after being tormented

461
00:26:36,161 --> 00:26:38,197
by Azuma, who abused his power."

462
00:26:41,700 --> 00:26:44,369
IT'S HORRIBLE! SO CRUEL
A PRODUCER WHO KILLS PEOPLE

463
00:26:44,436 --> 00:26:45,771
It says Riku is dead!

464
00:26:45,838 --> 00:26:47,506
- He's dead?
- The one from SS?

465
00:26:47,573 --> 00:26:51,710
K-pop is an industry that involves
the shaping of personalities.

466
00:26:51,944 --> 00:26:52,978
He tramples on

467
00:26:53,045 --> 00:26:55,380
the dreams of young people
who want to become stars

468
00:26:55,447 --> 00:26:59,551
and uses his authority as a producer
to control them with violence.

469
00:26:59,618 --> 00:27:02,855
As someone in the same industry,
there's no way I can forgive that.

470
00:27:03,722 --> 00:27:06,325
I was told that
Azuma has disappeared.

471
00:27:09,561 --> 00:27:10,696
To where?

472
00:27:11,396 --> 00:27:12,865
His whereabouts are unknown.

473
00:27:14,600 --> 00:27:15,934
You don't know where he is...

474
00:27:18,070 --> 00:27:19,438
Whatever shall I do?

475
00:27:20,572 --> 00:27:24,243
As his former colleague,
I'm very worried about him.

476
00:27:24,877 --> 00:27:27,412
I hope nothing bad happens to him.

477
00:27:27,746 --> 00:27:28,747
Don't you agree?

478
00:27:30,315 --> 00:27:31,583
At this time of year

479
00:27:33,218 --> 00:27:35,120
the snow must have
piled up high enough.

480
00:27:46,131 --> 00:27:47,432
What did you just say?

481
00:27:48,967 --> 00:27:49,968
It's nothing, sir.

482
00:27:51,103 --> 00:27:52,304
Excuse me.

483
00:28:00,145 --> 00:28:01,313
Hey!

484
00:28:02,347 --> 00:28:07,252
One, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight.

485
00:28:07,319 --> 00:28:12,057
One, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight.

486
00:28:12,124 --> 00:28:13,692
Hey, don't take photos!

487
00:28:13,759 --> 00:28:14,793
What?

488
00:28:17,129 --> 00:28:19,131
- You took photos, right?
- I did!

489
00:28:20,732 --> 00:28:22,434
They entered without permission.

490
00:28:23,468 --> 00:28:24,469
Seriously...

491
00:28:29,575 --> 00:28:30,742
I'm scared.

492
00:28:31,710 --> 00:28:33,045
They found out where we live, too.

493
00:28:33,545 --> 00:28:35,447
Where did Mr. Azuma go?

494
00:28:43,989 --> 00:28:46,959
Guys, what are your opinions?

495
00:28:47,859 --> 00:28:51,763
It's true that Mr. Azuma is strict.

496
00:28:54,566 --> 00:28:55,567
But...

497
00:28:58,036 --> 00:29:00,372
He isn't someone
who would use violence

498
00:29:01,873 --> 00:29:03,508
to force us to listen to him.

499
00:29:03,575 --> 00:29:04,843
I agree with you.

500
00:29:06,144 --> 00:29:07,312
I do, but...

501
00:29:10,782 --> 00:29:12,050
The leader of SS...

502
00:29:13,185 --> 00:29:16,788
His family said he killed himself
because Mr. Azuma abused his power.

503
00:29:17,723 --> 00:29:19,091
There's no room for doubt, is there?

504
00:29:27,599 --> 00:29:28,800
Kun and I...

505
00:29:30,469 --> 00:29:33,405
were invited by Ms. Park
to transfer to TORINNER.

506
00:29:33,605 --> 00:29:34,773
- What?
- What?

507
00:29:34,840 --> 00:29:35,874
Are you betraying us?

508
00:29:35,941 --> 00:29:37,843
- Both of you are leaving?
- Just hear us out.

509
00:29:41,146 --> 00:29:43,148
We turned her down, of course.

510
00:29:46,551 --> 00:29:49,154
But some arrogant man
came and told us...

511
00:29:50,522 --> 00:29:54,293
that it's over for
both Mr. Azuma and NAZE.

512
00:29:54,626 --> 00:29:56,395
What? What does that mean?

513
00:29:56,461 --> 00:30:00,666
That guy had the article
about Mr. Azuma's past.

514
00:30:00,732 --> 00:30:04,002
Does that mean
that guy framed Mr. Azuma?

515
00:30:04,536 --> 00:30:05,971
It's possible.

516
00:30:10,876 --> 00:30:14,613
Can't we do something
to help Mr. Azuma?

517
00:30:14,680 --> 00:30:16,548
But it has caused
such a huge commotion.

518
00:30:16,615 --> 00:30:18,650
What can we even do?

519
00:30:28,260 --> 00:30:29,394
I...

520
00:30:30,562 --> 00:30:32,331
want to protect NAZE.

521
00:30:33,598 --> 00:30:37,502
I think that's also
what Mr. Azuma wants.

522
00:30:40,072 --> 00:30:42,541
- Please let them perform.
- I'm sorry.

523
00:30:42,607 --> 00:30:45,744
I will get in touch again.

524
00:30:45,811 --> 00:30:47,112
Okay.

525
00:30:47,179 --> 00:30:49,114
Excuse me.

526
00:30:55,987 --> 00:30:57,222
Mr. Azuma!

527
00:30:57,289 --> 00:30:58,757
Where have you been?

528
00:31:15,307 --> 00:31:16,475
Mr. Azuma...

529
00:31:19,678 --> 00:31:21,747
I am really sorry.

530
00:31:25,851 --> 00:31:26,952
I...

531
00:31:28,820 --> 00:31:33,158
found Riku's letter at your home.

532
00:31:41,533 --> 00:31:44,202
Mr. Azuma, everything is ruined
since you left.

533
00:31:44,269 --> 00:31:45,437
What's this?

534
00:31:47,439 --> 00:31:48,974
UONUMA CITY, NIIGATA PREFECTURE
AONO RIKU

535
00:31:49,040 --> 00:31:51,410
"Aono Riku"?

536
00:31:53,145 --> 00:31:54,613
Riku from SS?

537
00:31:56,214 --> 00:31:58,517
What he wrote bothered me.

538
00:32:00,552 --> 00:32:03,054
So I went to the address
on the letter.

539
00:32:04,189 --> 00:32:07,125
That was when I met Riku's family.

540
00:32:07,192 --> 00:32:08,193
Leave!

541
00:32:08,593 --> 00:32:12,264
He said Riku killed himself
because of you.

542
00:32:13,398 --> 00:32:14,599
He said...

543
00:32:18,570 --> 00:32:20,038
you killed him.

544
00:32:24,876 --> 00:32:25,977
That's right.

545
00:32:31,349 --> 00:32:32,651
I pushed him too hard.

546
00:32:34,686 --> 00:32:35,720
And it killed Riku.

547
00:32:35,787 --> 00:32:37,022
Azuma, that's not true!

548
00:32:37,088 --> 00:32:38,223
Ms. Nam.

549
00:32:42,627 --> 00:32:43,862
Let's talk.

550
00:32:50,769 --> 00:32:52,938
Five, six, seven, eight.

551
00:32:53,004 --> 00:32:56,141
One, two, three, four, five...

552
00:32:56,208 --> 00:32:57,843
- Mr. Azuma!
- Mr. Azuma!

553
00:32:57,909 --> 00:32:59,010
- Where were you?
- Where did you go?

554
00:32:59,077 --> 00:33:00,445
Don't slack off!

555
00:33:02,747 --> 00:33:05,150
You bunch of useless losers.

556
00:33:05,517 --> 00:33:07,686
Do you think you can afford
to waste even a single second?

557
00:33:07,752 --> 00:33:10,589
You're running out of time
for your comeback, fools.

558
00:33:14,493 --> 00:33:15,794
Fools? What do you mean?

559
00:33:16,261 --> 00:33:18,897
What? I told you not to talk back.

560
00:33:18,964 --> 00:33:19,965
Do you want to get fired?

561
00:33:20,732 --> 00:33:23,368
Don't think we can be
like friends forever.

562
00:33:23,602 --> 00:33:24,603
Go on. Start now.

563
00:33:33,712 --> 00:33:36,147
Five, six, seven, eight.

564
00:33:36,214 --> 00:33:41,353
One, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight.

565
00:33:41,419 --> 00:33:43,955
What was that?
What are you trying to do?

566
00:33:44,022 --> 00:33:45,957
Five, six, seven...

567
00:33:46,024 --> 00:33:47,759
So useless, all of you.

568
00:33:47,926 --> 00:33:50,495
How can you guys
call yourselves idols?

569
00:33:50,862 --> 00:33:52,697
Stop! Stop! Stop!

570
00:33:52,864 --> 00:33:54,566
- Once more.
- Yes, sir.

571
00:33:54,633 --> 00:33:56,968
- Why can't you do something so easy?
- One, two, three, four...

572
00:33:57,035 --> 00:33:59,204
- Stop. Once more.
- Yes, sir.

573
00:33:59,271 --> 00:34:01,907
You all should quit!
I feel embarrassed watching!

574
00:34:02,107 --> 00:34:03,875
Stop. Once more.

575
00:34:04,442 --> 00:34:06,378
Stop. Once more.

576
00:34:07,145 --> 00:34:08,980
Six, seven, eight.

577
00:34:11,783 --> 00:34:15,153
Once more. Hurry up and begin.

578
00:34:16,187 --> 00:34:18,557
We've been practicing
since this morning.

579
00:34:19,491 --> 00:34:21,326
We'll get injured
if we don't take a break.

580
00:34:21,526 --> 00:34:23,828
The performance of a top artist
lasts over three hours.

581
00:34:23,929 --> 00:34:27,465
You need the stamina of an athlete.
You must know that. Right?

582
00:34:28,800 --> 00:34:31,937
You guys have no right to rest!

583
00:34:37,108 --> 00:34:38,610
That's enough!

584
00:34:41,212 --> 00:34:42,547
Why are you talking like that?

585
00:34:42,781 --> 00:34:45,850
Come again? What did you just say?

586
00:34:45,917 --> 00:34:47,686
I said that's enough!

587
00:34:49,988 --> 00:34:50,989
Kun!

588
00:34:51,790 --> 00:34:53,792
Don't act so cocky
towards your producer.

589
00:35:08,039 --> 00:35:10,842
Producer? Don't be ridiculous!

590
00:35:11,643 --> 00:35:14,145
You abandoned everything and ran away
when you were in trouble!

591
00:35:14,746 --> 00:35:16,748
You use violence
when things don't work out for you!

592
00:35:17,182 --> 00:35:20,418
How can you call yourself a producer?

593
00:35:21,353 --> 00:35:22,587
What did you just say?

594
00:35:22,654 --> 00:35:26,625
We won't follow a horrible person
like you. Get lost!

595
00:35:28,093 --> 00:35:29,427
- Mr. Azuma!
- No!

596
00:35:31,262 --> 00:35:32,397
- Don't do this!
- Stop!

597
00:35:33,298 --> 00:35:34,466
Please!

598
00:35:35,333 --> 00:35:36,368
Stop!

599
00:35:36,901 --> 00:35:39,037
Mr. Azuma, please!

600
00:35:39,104 --> 00:35:41,640
Mr. Azuma, please!

601
00:35:41,706 --> 00:35:43,875
Mr. Azuma, stop...

602
00:35:49,147 --> 00:35:51,383
I have an obligation
to protect the boys.

603
00:35:53,084 --> 00:35:55,754
I cannot continue to work

604
00:35:55,820 --> 00:35:57,656
with a violent man like you.

605
00:35:59,658 --> 00:36:01,693
Quit your job as producer at once

606
00:36:01,993 --> 00:36:04,396
and never appear
in front of them again!

607
00:36:16,641 --> 00:36:17,976
Fine by me.

608
00:36:18,510 --> 00:36:21,046
Not like I can afford to fool around
with leftovers like them forever.

609
00:36:21,112 --> 00:36:22,247
And that's my line.

610
00:36:22,981 --> 00:36:24,749
Don't ever appear
in front of me again.

611
00:36:41,533 --> 00:36:42,634
Kun!

612
00:36:45,336 --> 00:36:46,504
Kun!

613
00:36:49,607 --> 00:36:50,642
Kun!

614
00:37:09,928 --> 00:37:11,029
Kun!

615
00:37:11,730 --> 00:37:12,831
Kun!

616
00:37:16,234 --> 00:37:17,635
I'm sorry!

617
00:37:18,837 --> 00:37:20,105
Mr. Azuma!

618
00:37:21,039 --> 00:37:22,073
I'm sorry!

619
00:37:22,140 --> 00:37:24,442
It's okay. It's okay.

620
00:37:24,676 --> 00:37:25,677
I...

621
00:37:26,644 --> 00:37:31,249
I am only here because of Mr. Azuma.

622
00:37:35,186 --> 00:37:37,188
It was all thanks to Mr. Azuma!

623
00:37:40,325 --> 00:37:41,993
That's why I could do my best.

624
00:37:43,161 --> 00:37:44,529
But now...

625
00:37:45,230 --> 00:37:46,931
There's nothing I can do to help him!

626
00:37:47,932 --> 00:37:48,967
I'm sorry!

627
00:37:49,534 --> 00:37:50,668
I'm sorry!

628
00:37:50,902 --> 00:37:52,036
It's enough.

629
00:37:52,270 --> 00:37:54,939
- It's enough. Let's go back.
- I'm sorry!

630
00:37:58,276 --> 00:37:59,911
This time...

631
00:38:01,579 --> 00:38:05,016
It was supposed to be our turn...

632
00:38:06,718 --> 00:38:08,486
to protect Mr. Azuma.

633
00:38:09,120 --> 00:38:10,755
But we can't do anything.

634
00:38:11,923 --> 00:38:17,262
And yet, to protect us, Mr. Azuma...

635
00:38:19,063 --> 00:38:20,265
he intentionally...

636
00:38:21,199 --> 00:38:25,170
He intentionally abused us...

637
00:38:37,515 --> 00:38:39,651
- So you could tell, Kun?
- I'm sorry.

638
00:38:41,386 --> 00:38:43,988
Mr. Azuma, I'm sorry.

639
00:38:44,522 --> 00:38:45,657
Ms. Nam.

640
00:38:47,992 --> 00:38:49,294
Let's talk.

641
00:38:51,329 --> 00:38:53,798
- No.
- I am NAZE's producer.

642
00:38:55,133 --> 00:38:57,836
My job is to take the best course
of action for NAZE, right?

643
00:38:57,902 --> 00:38:59,204
But not that.

644
00:38:59,671 --> 00:39:00,672
What do you mean?

645
00:39:01,539 --> 00:39:03,208
What do you plan to do, Mr. Azuma?

646
00:39:05,043 --> 00:39:08,880
NAZE will be criticized if I stay.
So, I'll disappear.

647
00:39:09,013 --> 00:39:10,114
What?

648
00:39:11,449 --> 00:39:13,751
Of course you can't do that!

649
00:39:13,818 --> 00:39:16,454
Besides, the boys aren't going
to accept it!

650
00:39:16,521 --> 00:39:18,857
I'll make them think my past is true.

651
00:39:19,490 --> 00:39:21,659
- Work with me.
- But...

652
00:39:23,661 --> 00:39:25,230
If you do that

653
00:39:26,231 --> 00:39:29,434
you won't be able
to see the boys again!

654
00:39:34,205 --> 00:39:35,240
That's what I want.

655
00:39:36,407 --> 00:39:40,378
Besides, they'll be fine without me.

656
00:39:41,779 --> 00:39:43,014
Nam is here, too.

657
00:39:45,850 --> 00:39:47,318
And they've got you.

658
00:39:57,228 --> 00:40:01,332
He was acting all cool.

659
00:40:02,634 --> 00:40:06,337
Mr. Azuma smiled back then.

660
00:40:06,404 --> 00:40:07,605
When?

661
00:40:09,140 --> 00:40:12,777
When I lunged at him.

662
00:40:19,951 --> 00:40:24,489
It was for a split second,
but he had a slight smile.

663
00:40:25,823 --> 00:40:28,159
That was when I...

664
00:40:29,394 --> 00:40:32,030
He knew I would realize
what he was doing.

665
00:40:33,264 --> 00:40:34,999
It felt like he was telling me.

666
00:40:38,436 --> 00:40:40,171
I want to debut as early as possible!

667
00:40:40,238 --> 00:40:41,639
Your dream can't fill your stomach.

668
00:40:41,739 --> 00:40:42,774
I'm a fool.

669
00:40:42,840 --> 00:40:44,909
Even if you say it's a dream,
I still can't give up.

670
00:40:44,976 --> 00:40:48,346
I'm a fool, so I want to dream
a foolishly big dream!

671
00:40:48,413 --> 00:40:49,881
For a group of losers like you

672
00:40:49,948 --> 00:40:52,216
it's impossible to become
that 1 in 100,000.

673
00:40:52,283 --> 00:40:54,018
Impossible. It's absurd.

674
00:40:54,085 --> 00:40:56,955
But if we're doing it,
might as well aim to go global.

675
00:41:03,561 --> 00:41:06,631
Mr. Azuma gave up everything...

676
00:41:09,067 --> 00:41:10,735
to protect us.

677
00:41:12,470 --> 00:41:13,771
We must not...

678
00:41:16,641 --> 00:41:17,976
let his efforts go to waste.

679
00:41:19,944 --> 00:41:21,012
I will...

680
00:41:23,681 --> 00:41:25,083
NAZE will...

681
00:41:27,952 --> 00:41:29,754
definitely climb to the top!

682
00:41:33,491 --> 00:41:34,692
Yes.

683
00:41:49,440 --> 00:41:51,476
I would like to report something
regarding Mr. Azuma

684
00:41:51,542 --> 00:41:54,912
the producer who was embroiled
in a controversy a while ago.

685
00:41:55,513 --> 00:41:59,283
Two days ago, we suddenly
couldn't get a hold of him

686
00:41:59,917 --> 00:42:03,721
and his whereabouts are
still unknown to us.

687
00:42:05,089 --> 00:42:07,492
This is a serious breach of contract.

688
00:42:09,327 --> 00:42:10,561
As a result, we decided that

689
00:42:11,262 --> 00:42:14,932
as of today, we will cancel
our contract with Mr. Azuma.

690
00:42:17,435 --> 00:42:20,938
Oh, wow! NAZE's new song is so cool!

691
00:42:21,005 --> 00:42:22,473
I agree. I'm going to stan them!

692
00:42:23,541 --> 00:42:27,011
Still, I'm really happy
for NAZE's members.

693
00:42:27,378 --> 00:42:31,115
I can't believe that Azuma abuses
his power over these young guys.

694
00:42:31,282 --> 00:42:34,052
He's really horrible!
He's a demon! The devil!

695
00:42:36,454 --> 00:42:38,222
The new song is amazing!

696
00:42:38,289 --> 00:42:39,690
I'm so glad that guy is gone.

697
00:42:39,757 --> 00:42:41,726
- Right?
- Let's root for them.

698
00:42:42,126 --> 00:42:44,462
I know them from the news.
Isn't NAZE great?

699
00:42:44,529 --> 00:42:46,064
I know! Who's your fave?

700
00:42:46,130 --> 00:42:48,633
Their producer abused his power
and used violence.

701
00:42:48,699 --> 00:42:49,867
- NAZE.
- NAZE?

702
00:42:49,934 --> 00:42:52,370
They're admirable. I like them!

703
00:42:52,904 --> 00:42:54,705
VIEWS

704
00:42:57,175 --> 00:42:59,043
TOP 10 WEEKLY SALES RANKING

705
00:43:00,078 --> 00:43:01,179
First place.

706
00:43:01,679 --> 00:43:03,915
First place...

707
00:43:04,048 --> 00:43:05,783
RANKINGS WILL BE ANNOUNCED
AT 10:00 A.M.

708
00:43:05,850 --> 00:43:06,851
LOADING...

709
00:43:07,685 --> 00:43:08,853
Mr. Azuma...

710
00:43:26,404 --> 00:43:27,638
Congratulations, NAZE.

711
00:43:29,273 --> 00:43:30,675
We are all fools

712
00:43:30,908 --> 00:43:33,111
so we want to pursue
an even more absurdly big dream.

713
00:43:33,177 --> 00:43:36,547
Now, it's our turn
to help Mr. Azuma dream.

714
00:43:36,614 --> 00:43:39,117
Is that idiot
really not going to come?

715
00:43:39,517 --> 00:43:40,751
Let's do this!

716
00:43:40,985 --> 00:43:43,788
NAZE TO MAKE ITS WORLD DEBUT IN MAY

